  <info>
    <title>Managing virtual machines using &cockpit;</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="shalaka.harne@suse.com"/>
  </info>
  <para>
After clicking <guimenu>Virtual machines</guimenu>, you can view and create virtual machines, storage pools, and networks and import virtual machines. You can also manage virtual machines, storage pools, and networks in <guimenu>Virtual machines</guimenu>.
  </para>
  <para>You must install the <literal>kvm_server</literal> pattern to view <guimenu>Virtual machines</guimenu> in &cockpit; web console.
  </para>
<para>Using the Virtual machines screen,  you can perform the following tasks:</para>
  <itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Create virtual machines in <xref linkend="task-creating-cockpit-vm"/></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Modify virtual machine configurations in <xref linkend="modify-vm-configuration"/></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Import a virtual machine in <xref linkend="section-import-vm"/></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Clone a virtual machine in <xref linkend="section-clone-vm"/></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Rename a virtual machine in <xref linkend="section-rename-vm"/></para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Delete a virtual machine in <xref linkend="section-delete-vm"/></para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</topic>
